ce:section.ce:para:
FE-SEM technique was used to understand the morphology of β-CSO:Ce3+ (1–9 mol%) phosphors, CDs and 3wt%CDs@β-CSO:5Ce3+ composite (
                     Fig. 5a-h
                     ). The FE-SEM images of β-CSO:Ce3+ phosphor particles exhibited uneven and slightly aggregated flaky and rod like structure. However, with the increase of incorporation of Ce3+ ions in β-CSO, particles are found to be smooth and uniform diameter (Fig. 5a-f). Fig. 5g displays the FE-SEM image of CDs distinctly exhibit spherical particles with well-defined edges. Fig. 5h shows the FE-SEM image of 3wt%CDs@β-CSO:5Ce3+ composite clearly showed the CDs are embedded on the phosphor (enlarged view of Fig. 5h). From the using particle size distribution histograms, the average particle size was estimated and shown in Fig. 5i-l. As can be seen from the histograms, the estimated particle size is found to be ∼0.14 μm (β-CSO:5Ce3+) and ∼ 4.25 nm (CDs) respectively. However, in the case of 3wt%CDs@β-CSO:5Ce3+ composite the average particle size for phosphor and CDs is found to be ∼0.37 μm and ∼ 5.75 nm respectively.
